---
import SiteLayout from "../../../layouts/SiteLayout.astro";

const schema = {
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "FAQPage",
  "mainEntity": [
    {"@type":"Question","name":"What is sector rotation?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Sector rotation is an investment strategy that moves money between stock market sectors based on the current phase of the economic cycle. Different sectors outperform at different stages — technology and consumer discretionary tend to lead during early recovery, while utilities and consumer staples outperform during recessions. Investors use sector rotation to position portfolios ahead of economic shifts, overweighting sectors expected to benefit from the next phase."}},
    {"@type":"Question","name":"What are the 11 GICS sectors?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"The Global Industry Classification Standard (GICS) divides the stock market into 11 sectors: Information Technology (XLK), Health Care (XLV), Financials (XLF), Consumer Discretionary (XLY), Consumer Staples (XLP), Energy (XLE), Utilities (XLU), Industrials (XLI), Materials (XLB), Real Estate (XLRE), and Communication Services (XLC). Each sector has a corresponding SPDR Select Sector ETF that tracks S&P 500 companies in that sector."}},
    {"@type":"Question","name":"Which sectors perform best in a recession?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Defensive sectors historically outperform during recessions: Consumer Staples (XLP), Utilities (XLU), and Health Care (XLV). These sectors provide essential goods and services that consumers need regardless of economic conditions — food, electricity, and medical care. Consumer Staples stocks like Procter & Gamble and Coca-Cola have stable earnings even when GDP contracts. Utilities benefit from regulated revenue streams and high dividend yields that attract investors seeking safety."}},
    {"@type":"Question","name":"Which sectors perform best during economic recovery?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Cyclical sectors lead during economic recoveries: Consumer Discretionary (XLY), Financials (XLF), Industrials (XLI), and Technology (XLK). As the economy rebounds, consumers increase discretionary spending, banks benefit from rising loan demand, and industrial companies see growing orders. Technology often leads the sharpest recoveries due to pent-up enterprise spending. Real Estate (XLRE) also benefits from low interest rates that typically accompany early recovery phases."}},
    {"@type":"Question","name":"How do I track sector rotation?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Track sector rotation by monitoring relative performance across multiple timeframes (1-week, 1-month, 3-month, YTD). Rising sectors on shorter timeframes that are lagging on longer ones may signal a new rotation. Key indicators include: sector ETF relative strength vs. SPY, yield curve shape (steepening favors cyclicals), ISM Manufacturing PMI (above 50 favors industrials/materials), and consumer confidence (rising favors discretionary). Our tracker above provides real-time sector performance comparison."}},
    {"@type":"Question","name":"What are sector ETFs and how do they work?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Sector ETFs are exchange-traded funds that hold stocks from a single market sector. The most popular are the SPDR Select Sector ETFs, which divide the S&P 500 into 11 sector funds. Each ETF (like XLK for technology or XLF for financials) holds only companies classified in that GICS sector, weighted by market capitalization. They trade like stocks with real-time pricing, charge 0.09% expense ratios, and allow investors to overweight or underweight specific sectors without picking individual stocks."}},
    {"@type":"Question","name":"What is the best sector to invest in right now?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"The best sector depends on where we are in the economic cycle and your investment horizon. As of Q1 2026, Technology (XLK) and Communication Services (XLC) have shown strong momentum driven by AI infrastructure spending. However, sector leadership rotates — chasing recent performance often means buying near the top. A balanced approach overweights 2-3 sectors with favorable macro tailwinds while maintaining core diversification. Check our performance table above for current sector rankings across multiple timeframes."}},
    {"@type":"Question","name":"How does the economic cycle affect sector performance?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"The economic cycle has four phases that favor different sectors: (1) Early Recovery — interest rates are low, growth accelerates: Financials, Consumer Discretionary, Real Estate, and Technology lead. (2) Expansion — growth peaks, inflation rises: Technology, Industrials, and Materials outperform. (3) Slowdown — growth decelerates, rates peak: Energy, Health Care, and Consumer Staples gain. (4) Recession — GDP contracts, rates fall: Utilities, Consumer Staples, and Health Care provide safety. Understanding these patterns helps investors position ahead of turns."}}
  ]
};

export const meta = {
  title: "Sector Rotation Tracker — GICS Sector Performance & ETF Heatmap",
  description: "Track all 11 GICS sectors with SPDR ETF performance across 5 timeframes. Sector rotation model, economic cycle diagram, performance heatmap & current market positioning analysis.",
  category: "tool",
  published: "2026-03-21",
};
---

<SiteLayout
  site="westmount"
  title="Sector Rotation Tracker: 11 GICS Sector ETF Performance, Heatmap & Economic Cycle Model"
  description="Track sector rotation across all 11 GICS sectors with SPDR ETFs. Sortable performance table (1W to 1Y returns), economic cycle model, color-coded heatmap, and current market positioning analysis."
  canonical="https://westmountfundamentals.com/sector-rotation-tracker" schema={schema}
>
  <style is:inline>
.container{max-width:1200px;margin:0 auto;padding:0 20px}
a{color:var(--accent-color);text-decoration:none}
a:hover{text-decoration:underline}

header{padding:40px 0 20px;border-bottom:1px solid var(--border-color)}
.badge{display:inline-block;background:var(--accent-color);color:#fff;font-size:11px;font-weight:700;letter-spacing:1.5px;padding:4px 12px;border-radius:3px;text-transform:uppercase;margin-bottom:12px}
header h1{font-size:clamp(28px,4vw,42px);font-weight:800;line-height:1.15;margin-bottom:8px}
header p.subtitle{color:var(--text-secondary);font-size:18px;max-width:700px}
.meta{color:var(--text-secondary);font-size:13px;margin-top:12px;font-family:'JetBrains Mono',monospace}

.stats{display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(auto-fit,minmax(180px,1fr));gap:16px;margin:32px 0}
.stat{background:var(--card-bg);border:1px solid var(--border-color);border-radius:8px;padding:20px;text-align:center}
.stat .val{font-size:32px;font-weight:800;color:var(--accent-color);font-family:'JetBrains Mono',monospace}
.stat .label{font-size:13px;color:var(--text-secondary);margin-top:4px}

.table-section{margin:32px 0}
.table-section h2{font-size:22px;margin-bottom:12px}
.table-wrap{overflow-x:auto;border-radius:8px;border:1px solid var(--border-color)}
table{width:100%;border-collapse:collapse;font-size:13px}
th{background:#0c1428;color:var(--text-secondary);font-weight:600;text-transform:uppercase;font-size:11px;letter-spacing:.5px;padding:12px 14px;text-align:left;cursor:pointer;white-space:nowrap;border-bottom:1px solid var(--border-color);user-select:none;position:sticky;top:0}
th:hover{color:var(--accent-color)}
th.sorted-asc::after{content:' ▲';color:var(--accent-color)}
th.sorted-desc::after{content:' ▼';color:var(--accent-color)}
td{padding:10px 14px;border-bottom:1px solid var(--border-color);white-space:nowrap}
tr:hover{background:rgba(74,143,231,.06)}
.ticker{font-family:'JetBrains Mono',monospace;font-weight:600;color:var(--accent-color)}
.num{font-family:'JetBrains Mono',monospace;text-align:right}
.pos{color:#22c55e}
.neg{color:#ef4444}

.heatmap-section{margin:32px 0}
.heatmap-section h2{font-size:22px;margin-bottom:12px}
.heatmap-desc{color:var(--text-secondary);font-size:14px;margin-bottom:16px}
.heatmap-controls{display:flex;gap:8px;flex-wrap:wrap;margin-bottom:16px}
.heatmap-controls button{padding:6px 14px;border-radius:6px;font-size:12px;cursor:pointer;font-weight:600;border:1px solid var(--border-color);background:var(--card-bg);color:var(--text-primary);font-family:'JetBrains Mono',monospace}
.heatmap-controls button.active{background:var(--accent-color);color:#fff;border-color:var(--accent-color)}
.heatmap-grid{display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(auto-fit,minmax(160px,1fr));gap:8px}
.hm-cell{border-radius:8px;padding:16px;text-align:center;transition:transform .15s}
.hm-cell:hover{transform:scale(1.03)}
.hm-ticker{font-family:'JetBrains Mono',monospace;font-weight:700;font-size:18px;color:#fff}
.hm-name{font-size:11px;color:rgba(255,255,255,.8);margin:4px 0}
.hm-val{font-family:'JetBrains Mono',monospace;font-size:22px;font-weight:800;color:#fff}
.hm-legend{display:flex;justify-content:center;gap:6px;margin-top:12px;font-size:11px;color:var(--text-secondary);align-items:center}
.hm-legend-bar{height:10px;width:180px;border-radius:5px;background:linear-gradient(90deg,#dc2626,#ef4444,#f59e0b,#22c55e,#16a34a)}

.cycle-section{margin:32px 0}
.cycle-section h2{font-size:22px;margin-bottom:12px}
.cycle-desc{color:var(--text-secondary);font-size:14px;margin-bottom:20px;line-height:1.7}
.cycle-diagram{display:grid;grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr;gap:0;border-radius:12px;overflow:hidden;border:1px solid var(--border-color)}
.cycle-phase{padding:24px;position:relative}
.cycle-phase.recovery{background:rgba(34,197,94,.08);border-right:1px solid var(--border-color);border-bottom:1px solid var(--border-color)}
.cycle-phase.expansion{background:rgba(59,130,246,.08);border-bottom:1px solid var(--border-color)}
.cycle-phase.slowdown{background:rgba(245,158,11,.08);border-right:1px solid var(--border-color)}
.cycle-phase.recession{background:rgba(239,68,68,.08)}
.phase-header{display:flex;align-items:center;gap:10px;margin-bottom:12px}
.phase-num{width:28px;height:28px;border-radius:50%;display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:center;font-weight:800;font-size:13px;font-family:'JetBrains Mono',monospace}
.recovery .phase-num{background:#22c55e;color:#fff}
.expansion .phase-num{background:#3b82f6;color:#fff}
.slowdown .phase-num{background:#f59e0b;color:#fff}
.recession .phase-num{background:#ef4444;color:#fff}
.phase-name{font-size:18px;font-weight:700}
.recovery .phase-name{color:#22c55e}
.expansion .phase-name{color:#3b82f6}
.slowdown .phase-name{color:#f59e0b}
.recession .phase-name{color:#ef4444}
.phase-indicators{font-size:12px;color:var(--text-secondary);margin-bottom:10px;line-height:1.6}
.phase-sectors{display:flex;flex-wrap:wrap;gap:6px;margin-top:8px}
.phase-tag{font-size:11px;font-family:'JetBrains Mono',monospace;padding:3px 8px;border-radius:4px;font-weight:600}
.recovery .phase-tag{background:rgba(34,197,94,.15);color:#22c55e}
.expansion .phase-tag{background:rgba(59,130,246,.15);color:#3b82f6}
.slowdown .phase-tag{background:rgba(245,158,11,.15);color:#f59e0b}
.recession .phase-tag{background:rgba(239,68,68,.15);color:#ef4444}
.cycle-arrow{font-size:20px;color:var(--text-secondary);text-align:center;position:absolute}
.cycle-flow{text-align:center;margin-top:12px;color:var(--text-secondary);font-size:13px;font-family:'JetBrains Mono',monospace}

.positioning-section{margin:32px 0}
.positioning-section h2{font-size:22px;margin-bottom:16px}
.pos-grid{display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(auto-fit,minmax(280px,1fr));gap:16px}
.pos-card{background:var(--card-bg);border:1px solid var(--border-color);border-radius:8px;padding:20px}
.pos-card h3{font-size:16px;margin-bottom:8px}
.pos-card p{color:var(--text-secondary);font-size:14px;line-height:1.7}
.pos-indicator{display:inline-block;padding:3px 10px;border-radius:4px;font-size:11px;font-weight:700;font-family:'JetBrains Mono',monospace;margin-bottom:10px}
.pos-bullish{background:rgba(34,197,94,.15);color:#22c55e}
.pos-neutral{background:rgba(245,158,11,.15);color:#f59e0b}
.pos-bearish{background:rgba(239,68,68,.15);color:#ef4444}

.findings{margin:32px 0}
.findings h2{font-size:22px;margin-bottom:16px}
.finding-card{background:var(--card-bg);border:1px solid var(--border-color);border-radius:8px;padding:20px;margin-bottom:12px}
.finding-card h3{font-size:16px;margin-bottom:6px;color:var(--accent-color)}
.finding-card p{color:var(--text-secondary);font-size:14px;line-height:1.7}

.faq-section{margin:32px 0}
.faq-section h2{font-size:22px;margin-bottom:16px}
.faq-item{background:var(--card-bg);border:1px solid var(--border-color);border-radius:8px;margin-bottom:10px;overflow:hidden}
.faq-q{padding:16px 20px;font-weight:600;cursor:pointer;display:flex;justify-content:space-between;align-items:center}
.faq-q:hover{color:var(--accent-color)}
.faq-q::after{content:'+';font-size:20px;color:var(--text-secondary);transition:transform .2s}
.faq-item.open .faq-q::after{transform:rotate(45deg);color:var(--accent-color)}
.faq-a{padding:0 20px 16px;color:var(--text-secondary);font-size:14px;line-height:1.7;display:none}
.faq-item.open .faq-a{display:block}

.related-section{margin:32px 0}
.related-section h2{font-size:22px;margin-bottom:16px}
.related-grid{display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(auto-fit,minmax(240px,1fr));gap:12px}
.related-card{background:var(--card-bg);border:1px solid var(--border-color);border-radius:8px;padding:16px;text-decoration:none;transition:border-color .2s}
.related-card:hover{border-color:var(--accent-color);text-decoration:none}
.related-card h3{font-size:15px;margin-bottom:4px;color:var(--text-primary)}
.related-card p{font-size:13px;color:var(--text-secondary)}

.methodology{margin:32px 0;background:var(--card-bg);border:1px solid var(--border-color);border-radius:8px;padding:24px}
.methodology h2{font-size:18px;margin-bottom:12px}
.methodology p{color:var(--text-secondary);font-size:14px;margin-bottom:10px;line-height:1.7}

.disclaimer{margin:20px 0;padding:16px;border:1px solid var(--border-color);border-radius:8px;font-size:12px;color:var(--text-secondary);text-align:center;font-style:italic}
.updated-badge{display:inline-block;background:var(--card-bg);border:1px solid var(--border-color);color:var(--text-secondary);font-size:12px;padding:4px 10px;border-radius:4px;margin-top:8px;font-family:'JetBrains Mono',monospace}

footer{border-top:1px solid var(--border-color);padding:24px 0;text-align:center;color:var(--text-secondary);font-size:13px;margin-top:40px}

@media(max-width:640px){
  .stats{grid-template-columns:repeat(2,1fr)}
  .heatmap-grid{grid-template-columns:repeat(2,1fr)}
  .cycle-diagram{grid-template-columns:1fr}
  .cycle-phase.recovery{border-right:none}
  .cycle-phase.slowdown{border-right:none;border-bottom:1px solid var(--border-color)}
  .pos-grid{grid-template-columns:1fr}
  .related-grid{grid-template-columns:1fr}
}
  </style>

<div class="container">
    <h1>Sector Rotation Tracker: 11 GICS Sector ETF Performance</h1>
    <div class="updated-badge">Last Updated: March 2026</div>

    <div class="stats" id="stats"></div>

    <div class="table-section">
      <h2>Sector Performance Table</h2>
      <div class="table-wrap">
        <table>
          <thead>
            <tr>
              <th data-key="sector">Sector</th>
              <th data-key="ticker">ETF</th>
              <th data-key="w1" data-type="num">1-Week</th>
              <th data-key="m1" data-type="num">1-Month</th>
              <th data-key="m3" data-type="num">3-Month</th>
              <th data-key="ytd" data-type="num">YTD</th>
              <th data-key="y1" data-type="num">1-Year</th>
              <th data-key="weight" data-type="num">S&P 500 Wt</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody id="tbody"></tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="heatmap-section">
      <h2>Sector Performance Heatmap</h2>
      <p class="heatmap-desc">Color-coded performance grid — green signals outperformance, red signals underperformance relative to the broad market.</p>
      <div class="heatmap-controls" id="hmControls">
        <button data-period="w1">1-Week</button>
        <button data-period="m1">1-Month</button>
        <button data-period="m3" class="active">3-Month</button>
        <button data-period="ytd">YTD</button>
        <button data-period="y1">1-Year</button>
      </div>
      <div class="heatmap-grid" id="heatmapGrid"></div>
      <div class="hm-legend"><span>-10%</span><div class="hm-legend-bar"></div><span>+15%</span></div>
    </div>

    <div class="cycle-section">
      <h2>Sector Rotation Model: Economic Cycle</h2>
      <p class="cycle-desc">Sectors rotate in a predictable pattern through the four phases of the economic cycle. Understanding which sectors historically outperform in each phase helps investors position ahead of macro shifts.</p>
      <div class="cycle-diagram">
        <div class="cycle-phase recovery">
          <div class="phase-header">
            <div class="phase-num">1</div>
            <div class="phase-name">Early Recovery</div>
          </div>
          <div class="phase-indicators">GDP accelerating &middot; Low interest rates &middot; Earnings rebounding &middot; Credit expanding</div>
          <div class="phase-sectors">
            <span class="phase-tag">XLF Financials</span>
            <span class="phase-tag">XLY Cons. Disc.</span>
            <span class="phase-tag">XLRE Real Estate</span>
            <span class="phase-tag">XLK Technology</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="cycle-phase expansion">
          <div class="phase-header">
            <div class="phase-num">2</div>
            <div class="phase-name">Mid-Cycle Expansion</div>
          </div>
          <div class="phase-indicators">GDP strong &middot; Rising inflation &middot; Peak earnings growth &middot; Rates rising</div>
          <div class="phase-sectors">
            <span class="phase-tag">XLK Technology</span>
            <span class="phase-tag">XLI Industrials</span>
            <span class="phase-tag">XLB Materials</span>
            <span class="phase-tag">XLC Comm. Svcs</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="cycle-phase slowdown">
          <div class="phase-header">
            <div class="phase-num">3</div>
            <div class="phase-name">Late-Cycle Slowdown</div>
          </div>
          <div class="phase-indicators">GDP decelerating &middot; Peak rates &middot; Margin pressure &middot; Yield curve flattening</div>
          <div class="phase-sectors">
            <span class="phase-tag">XLE Energy</span>
            <span class="phase-tag">XLV Health Care</span>
            <span class="phase-tag">XLP Cons. Staples</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="cycle-phase recession">
          <div class="phase-header">
            <div class="phase-num">4</div>
            <div class="phase-name">Recession / Contraction</div>
          </div>
          <div class="phase-indicators">GDP contracting &middot; Falling rates &middot; Earnings declining &middot; Flight to safety</div>
          <div class="phase-sectors">
            <span class="phase-tag">XLU Utilities</span>
            <span class="phase-tag">XLP Cons. Staples</span>
            <span class="phase-tag">XLV Health Care</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="cycle-flow">Recovery → Expansion → Slowdown → Recession → Recovery ↻</div>
    </div>

    <div class="positioning-section">
      <h2>Current Market Positioning — Q1 2026</h2>
      <div class="pos-grid">
        <div class="pos-card">
          <span class="pos-indicator pos-bullish">OVERWEIGHT</span>
          <h3>Technology &amp; Communication Services</h3>
          <p>XLK and XLC continue to benefit from accelerating AI infrastructure spend and cloud migration. Technology leads all sectors YTD at +11.2%, driven by semiconductor demand and enterprise software renewals. Communication Services (+8.8%) is buoyed by digital advertising recovery and streaming profitability. Both sectors favor mid-cycle expansion positioning.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="pos-card">
          <span class="pos-indicator pos-bullish">OVERWEIGHT</span>
          <h3>Industrials &amp; Financials</h3>
          <p>Industrials (+5.6% YTD) benefit from reshoring trends, infrastructure spending, and defense budgets. Financials (+6.2%) are supported by a steepening yield curve and resilient loan demand. Both sectors historically outperform during mid-cycle expansion phases, aligning with current economic indicators showing solid GDP growth and moderate inflation.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="pos-card">
          <span class="pos-indicator pos-neutral">MARKET WEIGHT</span>
          <h3>Health Care &amp; Consumer Discretionary</h3>
          <p>Health Care (+3.8%) offers defensive characteristics with GLP-1 drug momentum providing a growth catalyst. Consumer Discretionary (+4.2%) is mixed — strong services spending but weakening goods consumption. Both sectors are transitional plays that work across multiple cycle phases, making them suitable for balanced positioning.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="pos-card">
          <span class="pos-indicator pos-neutral">MARKET WEIGHT</span>
          <h3>Materials &amp; Real Estate</h3>
          <p>Materials (+2.5%) are range-bound as China stimulus hopes offset global manufacturing weakness. Real Estate (+3.2%) is stabilizing as rate expectations moderate, though office vacancy remains a headwind. Both sectors need clearer macro catalysts before warranting overweight positions.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="pos-card">
          <span class="pos-indicator pos-bearish">UNDERWEIGHT</span>
          <h3>Energy</h3>
          <p>Energy (-1.8% YTD) faces headwinds from softening crude oil prices, rising US production, and weakening global demand forecasts. While valuations look attractive and dividends are well-covered, the sector needs oil above $80/barrel to sustain earnings growth. Late-cycle sector that typically outperforms closer to peak inflation.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="pos-card">
          <span class="pos-indicator pos-neutral">MARKET WEIGHT</span>
          <h3>Utilities &amp; Consumer Staples</h3>
          <p>Utilities (+5.8%) have surprised to the upside driven by AI data center power demand — a structural tailwind that transcends the traditional defensive narrative. Consumer Staples (+2.2%) lag as consumers trade down and margin pressures persist. Both offer portfolio ballast but lack near-term catalysts for outperformance.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="findings">
      <h2>Key Rotation Signals</h2>
      <div class="finding-card">
        <h3>Technology Leadership Remains Intact but Broadening</h3>
        <p>Technology and Communication Services account for nearly 40% of S&P 500 market cap and continue to dominate returns. However, Q1 2026 shows early signs of breadth improvement — Industrials and Financials are gaining relative strength on 1-month and 3-month timeframes, suggesting the rally may be broadening beyond mega-cap tech. This broadening pattern is typical of mid-cycle expansions and historically positive for overall market health.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="finding-card">
        <h3>Defensive Sectors Show Mixed Signals</h3>
        <p>Utilities are outperforming their typical late-cycle pattern thanks to AI-driven electricity demand, while Consumer Staples lag significantly. This divergence within defensives suggests the market is not pricing in imminent recession risk. Health Care sits in the middle — defensive by nature but with idiosyncratic growth from GLP-1 drugs. Watch for Utilities and Staples to move together as a recession warning signal.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="finding-card">
        <h3>Energy's Underperformance May Signal a Rotation Opportunity</h3>
        <p>Energy is the worst-performing sector YTD and one of the cheapest by forward P/E. Historically, Energy underperformance during mid-cycle phases creates attractive entry points — the sector tends to outperform during late-cycle and inflationary periods. With OPEC+ discipline holding and US Strategic Petroleum Reserve at low levels, any supply disruption could spark a sharp rotation into Energy names.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-section">
      <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
      <div id="faq"></div>
    </div>

    <div class="related-section">
      <h2>Related Tools &amp; Research</h2>
      <div class="related-grid">
        <a class="related-card" href="/etf-screener">
          <h3>ETF Screener</h3>
          <p>Screen 50 popular ETFs by category, expense ratio, AUM, dividend yield &amp; YTD performance.</p>
        </a>
        <a class="related-card" href="/stock-screener">
          <h3>Stock Screener</h3>
          <p>Screen 50 S&amp;P 500 stocks by market cap, PE ratio, dividend yield, sector &amp; 52-week performance.</p>
        </a>
        <a class="related-card" href="/sp500-companies-list">
          <h3>S&amp;P 500 Companies List</h3>
          <p>Complete list of all S&amp;P 500 companies with sector, market cap, and performance data.</p>
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="methodology">
      <h2>Methodology</h2>
      <p>Sector performance data is based on the 11 SPDR Select Sector ETFs that divide the S&P 500 into GICS (Global Industry Classification Standard) sectors. Returns represent price returns over the specified timeframes as of mid-March 2026. S&P 500 weight represents each sector's approximate market-cap weight in the index.</p>
      <p>The sector rotation model is based on historical patterns observed over multiple economic cycles. Actual sector performance may deviate from historical patterns due to structural shifts, policy changes, or idiosyncratic events. The current positioning analysis reflects macro conditions as of Q1 2026 and should be re-evaluated as economic data evolves.</p>
    </div>

